The error in the original unit test was due to an incorrect implementation of the `sortThird` method in the `SortThird` class. The fixed implementation of the method is as follows:

```java
package original;

import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.Collections;
import java.util.List;

class SortThird {
    public static List<Integer> sortThird(List<Integer> l) {
        List<Integer> l2 = new ArrayList<>(l);
        for (int i = 0; i < l.size(); i++) {
            if (i % 3 == 0) {
                List<Integer> subl = new ArrayList<>();
                for (int j = i; j < l.size(); j += 3) {
                    subl.add(l.get(j));
                }
                Collections.sort(subl);
                for (int j = i, k = 0; j < l.size(); j += 3, k++) {
                    l2.set(j, subl.get(k));
                }
            }
        }
        return l2;
    }
}
```

Now the unit test should pass without any errors.
